# CI/CD Deployment for a Static Website Using GitHub Actions

# 1. Set up your VM

# 2. follow instrutions to set up your VM in github+vm.md

# 3. Add GitHub secrets.

Add secrets:

HOST	VM Public IP
USERNAME	azureuser
SSH_KEY	Contents of github-actions-key
REPO_PATH  /var/www/New_repo 

# 4. Create GitHub Actions Workflow

Create:

.github/workflows/cicd.yml


# 5. Commit and Push


git add .
git commit -m "Setup CI/CD"
git push origin main
```



# 6. Verify Deployment

Visit:

http://YOUR_PUBLIC_IP


Every push to the `main` branch will now automatically deploy to the VM.

---

# Useful Commands

## Check Nginx Status

```bash
sudo systemctl status nginx
```

## Reload Nginx

```bash
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

## Check Firewall Rules

```bash
sudo ufw status
```

## Manually Pull Latest Changes

```bash
cd /var/www/YOUR_REPO
git pull origin main
```

